PN,44501
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1774023076
OL,3,CGerry Adams in London 'to assert the
OL,4,Clegitimacy of the republican cause'
OL,6,FGerry Adams has said he came to the
OL,7,FHigh Court in London "to reject the
OL,8,Fallegations" of him being behind three
OL,9,FIRA bombings in England and "to assert
OL,10,Fthe legitimacy of the republican
OL,11,Fcause".
OL,13,FHe commented after giving evidence in
OL,14,Fthe legal action he is defending
OL,15,Fagainst three men who were injured in
OL,16,Fthe bombings.
OL,26,@oD@VOUpD@LO]qD@]OUsD@FO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G1/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,446,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1774023076
OL,3,CGerry Adams in London 'to assert the
OL,4,Clegitimacy of the republican cause'
OL,6,FJohn Clark, a victim of the 1973 Old
OL,7,FBailey bombing in London; Jonathan
OL,8,FGanesh, a 1996 London Docklands
OL,9,Fbombing victim; and Barry Laycock, a
OL,10,Fvictim of the 1996 Arndale shopping
OL,11,Fcentre bombing in Manchester, all
OL,12,Fallege that Mr Adams was a leading
OL,13,Fmember of the Provisional IRA on those
OL,14,Fdates, including of its Army Council,
OL,15,Fand are seeking #1 in damages.
OL,17,FThe former Sinn Fein president told
OL,18,Fthe court earlier this week that he
OL,19,Fhad "no involvement whatsoever" in the
OL,20,Fbombings and was never a member of the
OL,21,FProvisional IRA.
OL,26,@{D@EOU{D@_O]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,446,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1774023076
OL,3,CGerry Adams in London 'to assert the
OL,4,Clegitimacy of the republican cause'
OL,6,FSpeaking towards the end of the trial,
OL,7,Fout of court, he said: "I'm restricted
OL,8,Fabout what I can say about these
OL,9,Fproceedings so I will limit myself to
OL,10,Freminding you that Irish people have
OL,11,Flong had a bad experience of British
OL,12,Fcourts, Irish republicans especially.
OL,14,F"However, I came to London to reject
OL,15,Fthe allegations levelled against me.
OL,17,F"And to assert the legitimacy of the
OL,18,Frepublican cause and the right of the
OL,19,Fpeople of Ireland to be free.
OL,26,@oD@XOUvD@AOUyD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,446,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1774023076
OL,3,CGerry Adams in London 'to assert the
OL,4,Clegitimacy of the republican cause'
OL,6,F"I am also here out of respect for the
OL,7,Fclaimants. I am very mindful of the
OL,8,Fmany other victims of the conflict.
OL,10,F"They too deserve our respect.
OL,11,FThankfully the war has been ended.
OL,13,F"As an Irish republican I am glad that
OL,14,Fwith others, I helped to secure this."
OL,16,FEdward Craven KC, for Mr Adams,
OL,17,Fquestioned on Thursday why the three
OL,18,Fmen took several decades to bring
OL,19,Ftheir claim, saying it should be
OL,20,Fdismissed for being brought too late.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@AOUuD@AOUvD@fO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,446,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1774023076
OL,3,CGerry Adams in London 'to assert the
OL,4,Clegitimacy of the republican cause'
OL,6,FHe said to the judge: "In Mr Clark's
OL,7,Fcase, we are dealing with a delay that
OL,8,Fis genuinely unprecedented in
OL,9,Fmagnitude.
OL,11,F"We say the very brief and bald
OL,12,Fhearsay evidence you have been
OL,13,Fprovided with falls a long way short
OL,14,Fof the kind of explanation that ought
OL,15,Fto be provided for a delay of this
OL,16,Flength."
OL,26,@nD@WOUsD@AOUxD@HO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,446,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1774023076
OL,3,CGerry Adams in London 'to assert the
OL,4,Clegitimacy of the republican cause'
OL,6,FHe also suggested the three men were
OL,7,Fusing the claim to try to have a
OL,8,F"public inquiry style" hearing into
OL,9,Ffinding historical truths, and asked
OL,10,Fthe court to focus on the three
OL,11,Fspecific bombings.
OL,13,FThe barrister said this could be an
OL,14,Fabuse of the court system, adding:
OL,15,F"One of the concerns we have had
OL,16,Fthroughout is that the claim is being
OL,17,Fused as a vehicle for a much wider
OL,18,Fexamination of Mr Adams's alleged role
OL,19,Fand actions."
OL,26,@pD@AOUpD@VO]wD@AOU{D@MO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,446,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1774023076
OL,3,CGerry Adams in London 'to assert the
OL,4,Clegitimacy of the republican cause'
OL,6,FIn statements to the court, the three
OL,7,Fmen said the reasons they did not
OL,8,Fbring claims earlier were that they
OL,9,Fdid not realise they could do so,
OL,10,Fcould not afford it, were suffering
OL,11,Ffrom mental or physical injuries and
OL,12,Ffeared violent reprisals.
OL,14,FAnne Studd KC, for the men, said on
OL,15,FThursday that it would be "unfair" if,
OL,16,Fafter the trial, the case was to be
OL,17,Fthrown out over an abuse of the court
OL,18,Fsystem.
OL,26,@wD@[OUwD@bO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,446,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44508
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1774023076
OL,3,CGerry Adams in London 'to assert the
OL,4,Clegitimacy of the republican cause'
OL,6,FShe said: "It is arguable and legally
OL,7,Funobjectionable, and these claimants
OL,8,Fare entitled to pursue it."
OL,10,FAt the start of the trial, she said
OL,11,Fthat a "jigsaw" of evidence from those
OL,12,Fwho knew Mr Adams and those who knew
OL,13,Fof him would prove the case against
OL,14,Fhim.
OL,16,FThat includes intelligence officers
OL,17,Fworking for the British authorities
OL,18,Fand former IRA volunteers.
OL,26,@nD@KOUpD@[O]sD@HOUsD@OO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G8/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,446,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44509
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1774023076
OL,3,CGerry Adams in London 'to assert the
OL,4,Clegitimacy of the republican cause'
OL,6,FOne anonymous member of British Army
OL,7,Fintelligence, known as witness A, said
OL,8,Fin a statement to the court last week:
OL,9,F"My own beliefs are that Adams would
OL,10,Fnot have been able to do what he did
OL,11,Fin the political arena if he had not
OL,12,Fbeen a member of the Army Council, and
OL,13,Fthis includes all the time up to the
OL,14,FCanary Wharf bomb in 1996."
OL,26,@qD@AOUvD@[O]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G9/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,446,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44510
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1774023076
OL,3,CGerry Adams in London 'to assert the
OL,4,Clegitimacy of the republican cause'
OL,6,FA second anonymous intelligence
OL,7,Fofficer, known as witness B, said last
OL,8,Fweek that if Mr Adams did not hold a
OL,9,Fhigh rank in the IRA, then he pulled
OL,10,Foff a "remarkable coup" in convincing
OL,11,Fthe British, Irish and US governments,
OL,12,Fas well as many IRA members, that he
OL,13,Fwas.
OL,26,@rD@GOUrD@WO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G10/12
